<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-909-790  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 909 790.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Nov 20 1989 v6 n46 p18(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Oregon C++ compiler for VAXes generates object code directly.andO;(from Oregon Software) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Slavin, Lois.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Oregon Software Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Oregon C++ (Compiler) (product introduction)DEC VAX (Minicomputer) (computer programs)VMS (Operating system) (computer programs).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionCompilers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Oregon C++ Compiler For VAXes Generates Object Code DirectlyandM;PORTLAND, Ore.andP;  -- Oregon Software has announced that Oregon C++ for VAX/VMSVersion 1.2A will be released next month.andP;  Oregon C++ is the first true C++for VMS, according to company officials.andM;Oregon C++ is not a translator to C.andP;  Instead, it directly generates objectcode, thereby eliminating the need for translation from C++ to C.andM;&quot;This direct generation of object code provides easier debugging and fasterprogram development, making it a true C++ compiler,&quot; said a companyspokesman.andM;Other major features include a source-level debugger, the NIH OOPS classlibrary, support of shared libraries, and a VAX C calling sequence.andP;  Thegeneral release next month will include complete compatibility with version2.0 of ATandamp;T's translator, cfont and a task library.andM;Oregon Debugger, the source-level debugger for Oregon C++, is capable ofdebugging C++, ANSI C and pre-ANSI C.andP;  It handles all standard C constructsand added language constructs of C++.andM;Oregon C++ uses VAXCRTL and is compatible with existing C libraries, whichcan be used without changes.andP;  Header files are included for systemdefinitions.andM;Interlanguage calling is available via the VAX C calling sequence.andP;  OregonC++ can call Pascal-2, Modula-2, Oregon C and any DEC language.andM;Oregon C++ can be called by another language as long as the main program iswritten in Oregon C++.andM;U.S.andP;  licensing fees range from $2,000 to $34,000, depending on machine,cluster or network configuration.andP;  The fee includes an ANSI C and Kandamp;Rcompiler.andM;Oregon C++ for VAX/VMS version 1.2A runs under VMS 5.0 and later.andM;For further information, Oregon Software Inc. can be contacted at 6915 S.W.andO;Macadam Ave., Suite 200, Portland, OR 97219-2397, (503) 245-2202.andO;</TEXT></DOC>